<title type="html"><![CDATA[Simple question about modern NES emulators]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5912&amp;p=54835#p54835"><![CDATA[
PocketNES on the GBA uses the GBA's hardware to render the background and sprites.  NesDS for the Nintendo Ds is based on PocketNES, so it does the same as well.<br /><br />That seems to be the way most emulators on the GBA/DS work, they use the 2D hardware instead of framebuffers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Jan 07, 2010 9:29 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
